As the human life expectancy increases, age-linked diseases have become more and 
more frequent. The worldwide increment of dementia cases demands medical 
solutions, but the current available drugs do not meet all the expectations. 
Recently the attention of the scientific community was attracted by natural 
compounds, used in ancient medicine, known for their beneficial effects and high 
tolerability. This review is focused on Ginger (Zingiber officinale) and explore 
its properties against Alzheimer's Disease and Vascular Dementia, two of the 
most common and devastating forms of dementia. This work resumes the beneficial 
