Cancer induced bone pain: current management and future perspectives.

Kapoor R(1), Saxena AK(1), Vasudev P(1), Sundriyal D(2), Kumar A(3).

Author information:
(1)Department of Anesthesiology and Pain Medicine, University College of Medical 
Sciences and GTB Hospital, New Delhi, India.
(2)Department of Medical Oncology, Hematology, All India Institute of Medical 
Sciences, Rishikesh, Uttarakhand, India. drdeepaksundriyal@gmail.com.
(3)Department of Pathology and Lab Medicine, All India Institute of Medical 
Sciences, Rishikesh, Uttarakhand, India.

Recent improvements in the therapeutic armamentarium of oncology by the addition 
of targeted and immunotherapeutic agents have led to an increase in the life 
expectancy of advanced-stage cancer patients. This has led to an increased 
